```julia
function timezone_bumper(dt::DateTime, bump=3)
    return dt + Dates.Hour(bump)
end

function timezone_bumper(dt::Date)
    throw(ArgumentError("Date type is not supported, please use DateTime type"))
end
```
This function `timezone_bumper` takes in a DateTime type `dt` and an optional `bump` argument which defaults to +3 hours. It returns the DateTime `dt` increased by the number of hours specified in `bump`. If a Date type is provided instead of a DateTime type, it will throw an ArgumentError indicating that Date types are not supported and to use DateTime types instead.
